# Lyl Valerie O. Busca — Personal Portfolio

A premium, modern, single-page portfolio website for **Lyl Valerie O. Busca**, Bachelor of Science in Information Systems student at Davao del Norte State College. Built with pure HTML5, CSS3, and vanilla JavaScript — no frameworks, no build tools, ready to deploy directly on GitHub Pages.

---

## Project Overview

This portfolio presents Valerie's academic background, experience (Researcher and UI Designer roles at the Institute of Computing), core skills (JavaScript, Figma, Research, Communication, Adaptability, Problem Solving), and projects in a clean, glassmorphism-inspired design with a professional teal-and-charcoal color palette. It's built to be recruiter-friendly, fully responsive, accessible, and fast-loading with zero external framework dependencies.

**Live sections:** Hero · About · Education · Experience · Skills · Projects · References · Contact

---

## Features

- **Glassmorphism design system** with a custom palette (`#1B2824`, `#304E4D`, `#4F7A78`, `#F5F7F6`, `#121A18`) and Poppins/Inter typography
- **Dark / Light mode toggle** with saved preference (`localStorage`) and system-preference detection
- **Sticky, scroll-aware navigation bar** with active-section highlighting
- **Mobile-first responsive navigation** with an animated hamburger menu
- **Typing animation** in the hero introducing the course title
- **Scroll-reveal animations** across every section (fade/slide/scale on entry)
- **Animated skill bars and percentage counters**
- **Animated stat counters** in the About section
- **Loading screen** with a branded animated mark
- **Smooth scrolling** between all in-page anchors
- **Interactive project cards** with hover overlays, tech badges, GitHub and Live Demo buttons
- **Animated vertical education timeline**
- **Contact section** with a client-side validated form (opens the visitor's email client — no backend required), contact cards, social icons, and a map placeholder
- **Circular profile photo** in the Hero section with a glassmorphism frame, soft shadow, and hover animation
- **Emphasized keyword styling** in section headings and the hero intro for a more editorial, less templated feel
- **Personality tag pills** in the About section (Analytical Thinker, Detail Oriented, Fast Learner, etc.)
- **Descriptive skill cards** — each skill pairs an icon, a one-line description, and an animated progress bar
- **Split first/last name fields** on the contact form
- **SEO**: meta description/keywords, canonical tag, Open Graph + Twitter Card tags, and JSON-LD structured data (`Person` schema)
- **Accessibility**: skip-to-content link, visible focus states, semantic landmarks, ARIA labels on icon-only controls, `prefers-reduced-motion` support
- **Back-to-top button** and footer with quick links and social icons

